properties.headline: COVID-19 Border Controls - NSW-QUEENSLAND M1 Pacific Motorway approaching Queensland border
properties.otherAdvice:
The Queensland state government has imposed restrictions on cross-border movements as a result of the coronavirus pandemic.

  • Queensland, Heavy & Exempt vehicles should remain on the motorway
  • All other vehicles must exit onto the Gold Coast Hwy where there will be a police checkpoint

Exemptions include freight, emergency vehicles and emergency workers, people travelling to and from work, court orders including family court, compassionate grounds and medical treatment.

During peak travel periods, particularly weekday mornings, extensive delays may be experienced by motorists travelling into Queensland.

Visit qld.gov.au for more details.

properties.headline: COVID-19 Border Controls - NSW-QUEENSLAND Cameron Corner Road
properties.otherAdvice:
The Queensland state government has imposed restrictions on cross-border movements as a result of the coronavirus pandemic.

Restrictions in effect include border road closures and police checks on vehicles on major highways.

Exemptions include freight, emergency vehicles and emergency workers, people travelling to and from work, court orders including family court, compassionate grounds and medical treatment.

  • Light vehicles must obtain a pass for travel. Application for a pass can be found at https://www.qld.gov.au/border-pass
  • Once you obtain a pass call Thargomindah Police Station on 07 4655 3200 for code to gate.
  • Heavy vehicles do not require a pass. Call Thargomindah Police Station on 07 4655 3200 for code to gate.       
  • Thargomindah Police Station is to be contacted during business hours ONLY.
  • Please call prior to travel as you will not have phone service at the gate/border.

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS June long weekend closure of Kosciuszko National Park - KOSCIUSZKO NATIONAL PARK Kosciuszko Rd
properties.otherAdvice:
The resort areas of Perisher, Thredbo and Charlotte Pass, and the Main Range of Kosciuszko National Park will be closed to the public for the June long weekend, from 4pm Fri 5 Jun to 5am Tue 9 Jun.

Road blocks will be in place to prevent public access up Kosciuszko Rd to Perisher, including Guthega and Smiggin Holes, and Charlotte Pass. The road will be closed at Wilsons Valley.

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS Parramatta Light Rail - WESTMEAD Hawkesbury Road between Darcy Road AND Hainsworth Street
properties.otherAdvice:
Hawkesbury Road, between Darcy Road and Hainsworth Street will be converted to one-way only in the northbound direction.

Hainsworth Street, between Hawkesbury Road and Park Avenue will also be converted to one-way only in the eastbound direction.

There will be no left turn from Hainsworth Street into Hawkesbury Road southbound.

These traffic changes will remain until 2023, when Parramatta Light Rail will be operational.

properties.otherAdvice:

properties.otherAdvice:

The intersection of Church and Ross Streets will be under traffic control management with one traffic lane maintained in each direction.

Eastbound motorists on Ross Street will not be able to turn left onto Church Street northbound. Motorists should use Villiers and Grose Streets to connect to Church Street northbound.

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS Parramatta Light Rail - ROSEHILL Grand Avenue between Durham Street AND Colquhoun Street
properties.otherAdvice:
From 7:30pm Friday 5 June, the westbound lanes on Grand Avenue will be permanently closed. Motorists will be detoured via Durham Street, Devon Street and Colquhoun Street to re-join Grand Avenue.  Please note that the westbound lane closures and detours will remain on Grand Avenue until 2023 when Parramatta Light Rail is operational.

Between 7:30pm Friday 5 June and 7am Saturday 6 June, Grand Avenue will be closed to traffic in each direction between Durham and Colquhoun Streets.

Between 7am Saturday 6 June and 5am Tuesday 9 June one of two eastbound lanes on Grand Avenue, between Durham and Colquhoun Streets, will also be closed.
